Advantages of Java:

Simple – Java has easy syntax and is easier to learn than C and C++. It does not use complex features like pointers and operator overloading.
Secure – Java reduces security risks by avoiding pointers and includes a Security Manager to protect programs.
Platform Independent – Java programs can run on any operating system that has the Java Virtual Machine (JVM). ("Write Once, Run Anywhere")
Object-Oriented – Java uses objects and classes, making programs easier to develop, reuse, and maintain.
Robust – Java has strong error handling and automatic memory management, making programs more reliable.
Multithreading – Java can run multiple tasks at the same time, improving performance.
Portable – Java programs can be moved and run on different devices without changing the code.
High Performance – Java provides good performance with the help of the Just-In-Time (JIT) compiler.
Distributed – Java supports network programming, making it suitable for distributed applications.
Dynamic – Java can load classes and libraries while the program is running, making it flexible.
